      "commit": {
        "parents": [
          {
            "commit": "9aaedeba704bd02c88ae6d2c8aef86f5af859382",
            "subject": "LU-16035 kfilnd: Initial kfilnd implementation"
          }
        ],
        "author": {
          "name": "Ian Ziemba",
          "email": "ian.ziemba@hpe.com",
          "date": "2020-06-04 19:56:43.000000000",
          "tz": -300
        },
        "committer": {
          "name": "Chris Horn",
          "email": "chris.horn@hpe.com",
          "date": "2022-07-27 15:15:06.000000000",
          "tz": -360
        },
        "subject": "LU-16035 kfilnd: Fix setting of transaction buffer",
        "message": "LU-16035 kfilnd: Fix setting of transaction buffer\n\nThe kfabric data transfer APIs do not allow for an offset to be\napplied to buffer. Instead, the kfabric API expects the buffer to have\nany user defined offset factored into it. Kfilnd was not taking this\ninto account. When LNet was passing kfilnd an IOV, this IOV was being\npassed into the kfabric API without taking into consider the offset\nand length of the IOV. This resulted in kfabric RMA operations with an\nincorrect size.\n\nTo resolve this issue, kfilnd_tn_set_buf() is defined. This function\nwill take the LNet IOV, apply the LNet offset and length, and store\nthe resulting IOV within the transaction structure. This new IOV will\nbe used for kfabric memory registration and data transfers.\n\nTest-Parameters: trivial\nHPE-bug-id: LUS-8908\nSigned-off-by: Ian Ziemba <ian.ziemba@hpe.com>\nChange-Id: Ied7929bf11255acaf72921a5a49e06ee76772c4f\n"
      },
      "branch": "refs/heads/master"
    }
  },
